PRACTICAL 3: Users, Groups, and Permissions
Prerequisites

• Practical 1 and 2 completed
• vCenter configured
• Windows Server ISO available

Steps

Create a new virtual machine for Windows Server 2016.

Allocate processors, RAM, storage, and select appropriate network adapter.

Install Windows Server 2016 operating system.

Open Server Manager and add Active Directory Domain Services role.

Promote the server to a Domain Controller by creating a new forest.

Configure domain name and set directory services password.

Restart server after promotion completes.

Configure static IP address and DNS settings.

Join vCenter Server Appliance to the Active Directory domain.

Add the domain as an identity source in vCenter.

View AD users and assign permissions to users and groups.

Test login using Active Directory credentials.
